      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 19</em>, <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 131</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 3 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 10 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 (small), 1d8 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x4; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> P; <strong>Special</strong> reach, trip</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Two-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Martial</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Polearms</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>This slender, 10-foot-long polearm has an added hook protruding from the head that is used to snag the clothing and armor of opponents. A hooked lance, unlike a lance, can't be wielded in one hand while mounted and doesn't deal extra damage if used while mounted.</p>",
